On August 6, 2021, the President signed four bills into law. The first one, H.R. 208, designates the United States Postal Service facility at 500 West Main Street, Suite 102 in Tupelo, Mississippi, as the Colonel Carlyle "Smitty" Harris Post Office. The second bill, H.R. 264, designates the facility at 1101 Charlotte Street in Georgetown, South Carolina, as the Joseph Hayne Rainey Memorial Post Office Building. The third bill, H.R. 772, designates the facility at 229 Minnetonka Avenue South in Wayzata, Minnesota, as the Jim Ramstad Post Office. Lastly, H.R. 1002, also known as the DEBAR Act of 2021, authorizes the Attorney General to issue an order prohibiting certain individuals from being registered to manufacture, distribute, or dispense controlled substances.